<input id="act_similarity_2", type="checkbox">
<div class="ACT_similar">
<li>Lim S , Yun J , Yoon H , Park C , Kim B , Jeon B , Kim D , Ryu S : Mlc regulation of Salmonella pathogenicity island I gene expression via hilE repression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24079299" target="_blank">24079299</a>]<br></li>
<li>Lim , S. , Yun , J. , Yoon , H. , Park , C. , Kim , B. , Jeon , B. , et al. ( 2007 ) Mlc regulation of Salmonella pathogenicity island I gene expression via hilE repression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24354910" target="_blank">24354910</a>]<br></li>
<li>Lim , S. , J. Yun , H. Yoon , C. Park , B. Kim et al. , 2007 Mlc regulation of Salmonella pathogenicity island I gene expression via hilE repression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25991823" target="_blank">25991823</a>]<br></li>
<li>Lim S , et al. ( 2007 ) Mlc regulation of Salmonella pathogenicity island I gene expression via hilE repression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22383560" target="_blank">22383560</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21059960" target="_blank">21059960</a>]<br></li>
<li>Mlc regulation of Salmonella pathogenicity island I gene expression via hilE repression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23554419" target="_blank">23554419</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19074398" target="_blank">19074398</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23006851" target="_blank">23006851</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17993530" target="_blank">17993530</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24835993" target="_blank">24835993</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25547794" target="_blank">25547794</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=28575106" target="_blank">28575106</a>]<br></li></div>
<li>For example , the type I fimbrial regulator , FimZ , increases HilE expression whereas the phosphoenolpyr-uvate phosphotransferase system ( PTS ) regulator , Mlc , represses it [ 23,24,35 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20686667" target="_blank">20686667</a>]<br></li>
<li>The Mlc regulon can be induced by glucose and , to a lesser extent , by mannose ( 39 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17329372" target="_blank">17329372</a>]<br></li>
<li>The Mlc protein binds to the hilE promoter .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17329372" target="_blank">17329372</a>]<br></li>
<li>These results clearly demonstrate that Mlc can regulate directly the hilE P3 promoter by binding to the promoter .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17329372" target="_blank">17329372</a>]<br></li>
<li>Mlc directly represses hilE by binding to the P3 promoter A gel mobility shift assay was performed with puriﬁed Mlc , to test whether Mlc directly represses the hilE P3 promoter .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17329372" target="_blank">17329372</a>]<br></li>
<li>Our data clearly demonstrate that Mlc directly regulates hilE expression by binding to the hilE P3 promoter ( Figure 5 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17329372" target="_blank">17329372</a>]<br></li>
<li>Membrane localization itself but not binding to IICB is directly responsible Glc for the inactivation of the global repressor Mlc in Escherichia coli .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17329372" target="_blank">17329372</a>]<br></li>
<li>Lim et al. have reported that an mlc mutant shows decreased expression of hilD , hilA , and invF and that Mlc can directly bind to the hilE promoter .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23554419" target="_blank">23554419</a>]<br></li>
<li>Based on these results , we propose that Mlc functions to sense the availability of sugars and is linked to virulence gene regulation by its ability to control hilE expression in Salmonella .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17329372" target="_blank">17329372</a>]<br></li>
<li>Salmonella may use Mlc to sense the availability of sugars , thereby allowing decisions as to when and where to initiate the expression of genes involved in invasion .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17329372" target="_blank">17329372</a>]<br></li>
<li>The specific down-regulation of hilD observed in the presence of Mlc regulon-inducible sugars , such as glucose and mannose , could not be detected in the mlc mutant .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17329372" target="_blank">17329372</a>]<br></li>
<li>We observed a 2-fold activation of hilE and concomitant repression of hilD in the presence of glucose or mannose , which are known inducers of the Mlc regulon , when TB was used ( Figure 6 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17329372" target="_blank">17329372</a>]<br></li>
<li>The hilE gene , which encodes a negative regulator of SPI-1 gene expression , possesses three promoters , one of which is controlled by the Mlc repressor ( Lim et al. , 2007 ) , which responds to the availability of glucose , and another that is controlled by the FimZ activator ( Baxter and Jones , 2005 ) , which also regulates Salmonella attachment and adherence under static growth conditions .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21570144" target="_blank">21570144</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , the effects of Mlc on hilD expression and bacterial invasiveness were not seen in the hilE mutant , and hilE expression was increased in the mlc mutant , which suggests that Mlc exerts positive effects on the expression of SPI1 genes by reducing the expression of HilE , which is known to downregulate the expression of SPI1 genes through direct interaction with HilD .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17329372" target="_blank">17329372</a>]<br></li>
<li>Primers for real-time PCR analysis Primer sequence ( 50 to 30 ) Gene Forward Reverse Size ( bp ) GTCCGGTCGTAGTGGTGTCT TGTCGCACCAGTATCAGGAG AAAGCCGGATCAAAGGTTTT CGGGGAGGAAGGTGTTGTG CGGCAGTTCTTCGTAATGGT AAATAGCGCGAAACTCAGGA CTTTCACCGTTTTCCCGTTA CAGCCCGGGGATTTCACATC hilA invF hilE rrs The expression levels of hilA , invF and hilD , but not of hilC , are decreased in the mlc mutant To identify the target gene in SPI1 that is regulated by Mlc , the expression patterns of the SPI1-regulatory genes , which include hilA , invF , hilC and hilD , were examined by primer extension analysis of total RNA from SL1344 and SR1304 grown statically to the exponential phase .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17329372" target="_blank">17329372</a>]<br></li>
<li>Sugars that induce the Mlc regulon repress hilD expression by activating hilE Sequestration of Mlc by the unphosphorylated form of glucose permease , enzyme IICB , is known to displace Glc Mlc from its DNA-binding sites , thereby allowing transcription of its target genes ( 25 -- 27 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17329372" target="_blank">17329372</a>]<br></li>
<li>The results presented in this study support the notion that hilE expression is activated as a result of Mlc sequestration by unphosphorylated EIICB in the Glc presence of glucose .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17329372" target="_blank">17329372</a>]<br></li>
<li>The relativel high glucose concentration in the proximal small intestine may repress SPI1 gene expression through Mlc , perhaps together with PhoR-PhoB and/or SirA , whereas upon transit to the distal ileum , the glucose concentration becomes low enough to activate the invasion genes of SPI1 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17329372" target="_blank">17329372</a>]<br></li>
<li>Expression of ptsG , the gene for the major glucose PTS transporter in Escherichia coli , is repressed by Mlc and induced by growth-on-glucose .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23935052" target="_blank">23935052</a>]<br></li>
